            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;You can improve this to support member functions with template arguments.  Change template &amp;lt;typename T&amp;gt; to template &amp;lt;typename T, typename ... Args&amp;gt;, then you can use &quot;Args...&quot; in your macro elipsis to create a check struct with variadic template args. eg. Detect &quot;void onNext(const T &amp;amp;)&quot; method &lt;code&gt;HAS_MEM_FUNC( onNext, has_memberfn_onNext, void, Args... );&lt;/code&gt;     ... &lt;code&gt;template &amp;lt;typename V&amp;gt;     struct Foo { 	void onNext(const V &amp;amp;);         static_assert&amp;lt; has_memberfn_onNext&amp;lt;Foo&amp;lt;V&amp;gt;,const V &amp;amp;&amp;gt;::value, &quot;API fail&quot; );     };&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

