            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Is there way to inline the &lt;code&gt;has_foo&lt;/code&gt; into the template call of &lt;code&gt;is_supported&lt;/code&gt;. What I would like is to call something like: &lt;code&gt;std::cout &amp;lt;&amp;lt; is_supported&amp;lt;magic.foo(), struct1&amp;gt;::value &amp;lt;&amp;lt; std::endl;&lt;/code&gt;. The reason for this, I want to define a &lt;code&gt;has_foo&lt;/code&gt; for each different function signature that I want to check before I can check for the function?&lt;/span&gt;

